do all of these things

251
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:01,650
sooner rather than later.

252
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:04,470
Let me know in the comments
how many you've ticked off.

253
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:06,900
Number one, open your own bank accounts.

254
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,570
Having your own bank accounts
that only you have access to

255
00:10:09,570 --> 00:10:11,820
is the first logical step you should take

256
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,800
once you're over the age of 18.

257
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:16,590
I say accounts because, really and truly,

258
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:18,030
you should have two.

259
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,890
The first is a current account,

260
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:22,890
or as the Americans call
it, a checking account.

261
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:25,620
This is where your money
should flow in and out.

262
00:10:25,620 --> 00:10:28,080
For example, let's say
you got yourself a job

263
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,250
at a coffee shop.

264
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:32,550
The coffee shop pays your wage
into your current account,

265
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:35,550
and then you can use that money
on whatever you want really.

266
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:38,610
The second is a high-interest
savings account.

267
00:10:38,610 --> 00:10:41,250
This is where you should start
building up an emergency fund

268
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,740
of three to six months
of your living expenses

269
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:46,230
just in case something out
of your control happens

270
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:47,940
and your income dries up.

271
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:50,940
It's like when you chug
a big pot shield potion

272
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:53,460
on "Fortnite," but keep some minis handy.

273
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:56,070
So where should you
open up these accounts?

274
00:10:56,070 --> 00:10:58,140
Well, you need to be looking for banks

275
00:10:58,140 --> 00:10:59,970
that don't charge high fees.

276
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:01,710
I remember I used to get charged

277
00:11:01,710 --> 00:11:04,290
for stupid little things all the time.

278
00:11:04,290 --> 00:11:06,810
Having these accounts
shouldn't cost you money.

279
00:11:06,810 --> 00:11:08,850
I also think you should have two accounts

280
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:10,110
with different banks,

281
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:13,230
as it makes your savings
way less easier to spend.

282
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:15,480
When it's outta sight, it's outta mind.

283
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,610
If you're in the UK,
then I'd recommend going

284
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:20,760
with a challenger bank like
Monzo for your current account.

285
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,230
Now, this isn't sponsored,

286
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:25,020
but their app is genuinely very good.

287
00:11:25,020 --> 00:11:27,450
For your savings account,
Chase is a great option,

288
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:30,540
as they're currently offering
4.1% interest on your money,

289
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:32,970
so you'll get paid for just leaving

290
00:11:32,970 --> 00:11:34,110
your money in the account.

291
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,050
In the USA, I would recommend
looking at Ally Bank

292
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:39,840
or Bank of America because
they offer minimal fees

293
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,360
and have really strong
online banking service.

294
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,910
Number two, get a credit card.

295
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:47,430
When I was younger, I believe
that if you never borrowed,

296
00:11:47,430 --> 00:11:49,410
you'd have an amazing credit score,

297
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:52,560
since you never took out a
loan or made any late payments.

298
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,790
It makes sense, right?

299
00:11:53,790 --> 00:11:57,510
Well, that couldn't be
further from the truth.

300
00:11:57,510 --> 00:11:59,820
Taking out a credit card when you turn 18

301
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:02,670
is the perfect tool to
build up your credit score.

302
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:04,710
You can do this by using your credit card

303
00:12:04,710 --> 00:12:07,590
to pay for the things you
would normally pay for in cash,

304
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:10,860
like paying for the gas
in your car, for example,

305
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:12,690
and then paying the card off in full

306
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,850
every month without fail.

307
00:12:14,850 --> 00:12:17,820
Using it this way will ensure
that you never get charged

308
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:20,280
any interest at the
same time as building up

309
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,180
your credit score.

310
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:24,120
A credit score is kind of
like you're Uber rating

311
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,380
but for money.

312
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,480
Banks look at this and then they decide

313
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,460
whether or not they're
gonna give you a loan,

314
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:32,610
and if they do, what interest
rate they're gonna charge you.

315
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:34,470
Now, lots of people are against the idea

316
00:12:34,470 --> 00:12:35,640
of getting a credit card

317
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,770
because they're taught
from a really young age

318
00:12:37,770 --> 00:12:39,090
that debt is bad.

319
00:12:39,090 --> 00:12:43,020
I know this because that's
exactly what I was taught.

320
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:47,490
My dad would always say, "Never
a lender or a borrower be."

321
00:12:47,490 --> 00:12:50,160
This was a saying that
originally came from rich people

322
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,400
years and years ago to
keep the workers down,

323
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:56,310
as they knew, by borrowing,
the working class

324
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:58,350
could create wealth for themselves.

325
00:12:58,350 --> 00:13:00,330
The rich wanted to keep getting richer

326
00:13:00,330 --> 00:13:02,250
and keep the poor in their place.

327
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,290
If I had a credit card when I was 18,

328
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:07,410
it would've been much easier
to get a mortgage sooner

329
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:09,180
and buy my first property.

330
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:11,670
I would've also been
able to borrow more money

331
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,380
at lower interest rates.

332
00:13:13,380 --> 00:13:16,170
Now, that may not sound significant,

333
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,750
but over a long period, like a mortgage,

334
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,190
this can really add up.

335
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:22,710
Number three, open an invest in account.

336
00:13:22,710 --> 00:13:25,860
The key is to open the
correct type of account.

337
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:28,380
You'll often hear people
throwing around terms

338
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:33,000
like Roth IRA in the USA,
stocks and shares ISA in the UK,

339
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,870
and TFSA in Canada, and
supers in Australia.

340
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,550
So if you don't have
one of these accounts,

341
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:41,430
then you're missing out,
as they allow you to avoid

342
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:43,590
having to pay taxes on your investments.

343
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:47,100
But they do have limits because
they're extremely powerful.

344
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,250
Nowadays, opening an investing
account is very simple,

345
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:52,230
as you can do it all
from your mobile phone.

346
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:54,150
A great thing about these investing apps

347
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:55,920
is that it actually gives you the ability

348
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:57,420
to buy fractional shares.

349
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:02,010
So rather than having to
pay $220 for an Apple share,

350
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:04,110
you can invest as little as $1.

351
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:07,020
Now, I wish I had this
option when I was younger,

352
00:14:07,020 --> 00:14:09,750
as it would've allowed me to
get in some early experience

353
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:12,540
with investing without
having to take any big risks.

354
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:16,080
One of my favorite investing
platforms is Trading 212,

355
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,520
as they offer fractional shares

356
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:19,680
and also stocks and shares ISAs.

357
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,870
Since I was planning to
talk about their app anyway,

358
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:24,180
I reached out to them to
see if they'd be interested

359
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:26,490
in sponsoring this portion of the video.

360
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,620
They agreed, and are offering a free stock

361
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:30,900
worth of up to 100 pound to anyone

362
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:33,810
that uses the code Tilbury
when they create an account.

363
00:14:33,810 --> 00:14:36,660
Plus, you can get more free
stocks by inviting your friends.

364
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:38,520
Both of you will get a free share

365
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,200
as long as they fund their account.

366
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,420
If you aren't quite
ready to invest for real,

367
00:14:42,420 --> 00:14:45,120
one of the really cool
things about Trading 212

368
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:48,300
is they let you practice
investing with fake money.

369
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,010
You can get familiar with the markets

370
00:14:50,010 --> 00:14:53,610
using real data without
risking any actual money.

371
00:14:53,610 --> 00:14:55,860
So if you're a little
uncomfortable with investing

372
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:58,050
or just want to try out some strategies

373
00:14:58,050 --> 00:15:00,270
before putting your own money on the line,

374
00:15:00,270 --> 00:15:02,670
this is a great way to get started.

375
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:05,340
Also, don't worry if you've
already opened an account

376
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:06,750
within the last 10 days.

377
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:09,360
You can still use a promo
code Tilbury in the app

378
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,710
and receive your free share.

379
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:13,230
So feel free to pause a video right now,

380
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:15,720
get your free stock, and
then continue watching.

381
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,960
Number four, carefully
consider university.

382
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,767
So many teenagers have asked me,

383
00:15:20,767 --> 00:15:22,980
"Is going to university a scam?"

384
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:26,190
My answer is always yes and no.

385
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:27,720
On one hand, for some careers,

386
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,730
you certainly need to go to university

387
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:32,370
like doctors, nurses, and teachers.

388
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:33,690
There is a direct result

389
00:15:33,690 --> 00:15:36,060
from doing university courses like this.

390
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,330
You get a degree, and the
career path opens up to you.

391
00:15:39,330 --> 00:15:42,480
These professions play
critical roles in our society

392
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:45,240
directly impacting the way we function,

393
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,970
so are absolutely not a scam.

394
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:50,820
I actually think these types
of courses should be free

395
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:53,460
and reserved for the
people with the best grades

396
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:56,010
and passion for following
one of these careers.

397
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:58,470
However, on the other hand,
there are a lot of other courses

398
00:15:58,470 --> 00:16:01,770
out there that don't open up
job opportunities directly,

399
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:03,810
and therefore, why waste your money

400
00:16:03,810 --> 00:16:07,290
and, more importantly, your
time studying at university

401
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:09,090
for something you don't really need?

402
00:16:09,090 --> 00:16:12,120
Skill trades like
plumbing, entrepreneurship

403
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:15,180
and tech, well, they
don't require a degree.

404
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:17,880
It's more about how good
you are at what you do.

405
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:20,910
Your track record and results
will speak for itself.

406
00:16:20,910 --> 00:16:23,340
I mean, I read through
my comments on here,

407
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:26,250
and I've seen lots of people
claim they've learned more

408
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,040
from me than they did in
their business degree.

409
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:31,080
Now, that really says a lot.

410
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:33,540
For me, and for a lot of other employers,

411
00:16:33,540 --> 00:16:36,030
it's more about your practical experience

412
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:38,370
and attitude than anything else.

413
00:16:38,370 --> 00:16:41,880
So please, don't be pressured
into go into university

414
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,950
to study something you don't care about

415
00:16:43,950 --> 00:16:45,900
and waste four years of your life.

416
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:48,930
I mean, I heard there's a
golf management degree now.

417
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:52,050
How ridiculous. Personally, I love golf.

418
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:53,610
I just want a major competition

419
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:55,500
called The Duke of Edinburgh Cup.

420
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,970
I didn't need to go to university

421
00:16:56,970 --> 00:16:59,160
to learn how to play or manage the game.

422
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,140
It's laughable. It really is.

423
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:03,330
Look, if you really dunno
what to do with your life,

424
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:05,550
my advice would be to
get an apprenticeship.

425
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:07,350
They were huge back in my day,

426
00:17:07,350 --> 00:17:10,290
and they're coming back and
getting more popular than ever.

427
00:17:10,290 --> 00:17:12,750
Plus, you get paid what you're learning.

428
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:15,000
It's a win-win situation, if you ask me.

429
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,310
So will those schools,
then maybe your mates

430
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:19,860
will try and push you to go to university,

431
00:17:19,860 --> 00:17:22,260
think about what you really want.

432
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,420
Think about the 60 to 100k of debt

433
00:17:24,420 --> 00:17:26,340
that you could have
wrapped around your neck

434
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:29,340
and ask yourself, is it
worth paying that off

435
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:30,900
for the whole of your life?

436
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,270
Number five, avoid bad debt.

437
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:36,240
Debt is like a heavy
anchor that drags you down,

438
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,670
slowing your progress and holding you back

439
00:17:38,670 --> 00:17:40,620
from reaching your full potential.

440
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:42,720
Don't get me wrong, in some cases,

441
00:17:42,720 --> 00:17:44,550
you can use debt to your advantage,

442
00:17:44,550 --> 00:17:47,160
like when buying a property, for example.

443
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:49,470
Taking on a mortgage to buy real estate

444
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:51,450
can be a really smart investment

445
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:54,360
because property can go up
in value as time goes by.

446
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:56,550
By using this debt strategically,

447
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:59,040
you can leverage this
borrowed money to have access

448
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:01,290
to these assets that
will hopefully increase

449
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,820
your long term net worth.

450
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:05,310
The same goes for having
your own business.

451
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:07,680
If you borrow moneys to
start your own business

452
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:10,890
and it takes off, you can
make some serious profit.

453
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:14,280
Without that initial money,
you might never be successful.

454
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,230
I know that was the case
for me when I opened up

455
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:18,150
my first radio control model shop.

456
00:18:18,150 --> 00:18:20,850
Without a loan, I simply
couldn't have started.

457
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,650
However, there is a type of debt

458
00:18:22,650 --> 00:18:27,240
you should avoid at all costs,
and this is consumer debt.

459
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,430
If you can't afford to
buy something outright

460
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:31,560
that isn't going to create wealth,

461
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,720
then you shouldn't buy it.

462
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,730
A lot of people finance their cars,

463
00:18:35,730 --> 00:18:38,520
and this is just one example
of where borrowing money

464
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,830
actually leaves you worse
off in the long run.

465
00:18:40,830 --> 00:18:44,610
Here in the UK, a shocking
2.2 million drivers

466
00:18:44,610 --> 00:18:47,430
finance their cars, and I'm willing to bet

467
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:49,650
most of them are stuck in this money trap.

468
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:52,260
I understand that you might
wanna drive a certain car.

469
00:18:52,260 --> 00:18:55,530
Now, I love cars, so I
totally understand that.

470
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:58,740
I get it, but is it really worth it?

471
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:00,270
Just something for you to think about.

472
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:02,760
Number six, start a side hustle.

473
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:05,037
Most people's advice when you turn 18 is,

474
00:19:05,037 --> 00:19:06,570
"Go and get a job."

475
00:19:06,570 --> 00:19:08,700
They make it sound so miserable,

476
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:11,108
and it's like you get no
choice with your life.

477
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:13,170
That's what you're expected to do.

478
00:19:13,170 --> 00:19:15,690
Go to your job and be miserable.

479
00:19:15,690 --> 00:19:18,840
Well, let me tell you, it
doesn't have to be this way.

480
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,730
You don't have to wake up every morning

481
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:22,950
thinking that you're
stuck and not progressing.

482
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:24,840
If you follow this video so far,

483
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,580
you'll have some valuable skills,

484
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:30,030
and you can use them to start
a service-based side hustle.

485
00:19:30,030 --> 00:19:31,770
This type of side hustle is great.

486
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:35,430
Think copywriting, video
editing, videography,

487
00:19:35,430 --> 00:19:38,100
web development, and community management.

488
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:41,040
All of these require very
little startup money.

489
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,590
You just need to master
the skill inside and out.

490
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:45,840
If you haven't got a
high-income skill yet,

491
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,610
then you really need to catch up.

492
00:19:47,610 --> 00:19:50,910
So no matter what job you
go and get, leverage it.

493
00:19:50,910 --> 00:19:53,640
Use the skills it gives
you and the money you make

494
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:56,760
to transform your daily
grind into a launch pad

495
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:57,960
for greater things.

496
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,000
Even if you can't learn
any skills from it,

497
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,330
use it as motivation to put in
the extra work on the weekend

498
00:20:03,330 --> 00:20:04,950
to learn a valuable skill

499
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:07,590
and improve your current situation.

500
00:20:07,590 --> 00:20:09,510
Start viewing it like this.

501
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:13,740
Every shift you dread is an
investment towards your future.

502
00:20:13,740 --> 00:20:16,650
Number seven, invest for the long term.

503
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:19,830
Compound interest is an
extremely powerful law,

504
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:22,110
especially when it comes to investing.

505
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:24,540
It means that not only
will you earn an interest

506
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:28,050
on your initial investment,
but you also earn interest

507
00:20:28,050 --> 00:20:30,540
on the interest that
you've already earned.

508
00:20:30,540 --> 00:20:32,580
This can lead to your money growing bigger

509
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:34,020
and bigger over time.

510
00:20:34,020 --> 00:20:35,910
It's like when you create that snowball

511
00:20:35,910 --> 00:20:38,490
and roll it down the hill,
it just keeps getting bigger

512
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:41,580
and bigger and bigger the more
snow that's packed onto it.

513
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:46,530
For example, let's say you
invest $250 a month at age 18

514
00:20:46,530 --> 00:20:50,220
into a Roth IRA or a
stocks and shares ISA.

515
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:53,070
Assuming an average yearly return of 8%

516
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:55,860
by the age of 65, your
investment could grow

517
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:59,250
to approximately $1.5 million tax free.

518
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:02,340
Now, if we compare this to
someone who starts investing

519
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:07,110
the same amount at age
28, by the age he's 65,

520
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:11,670
their investment would
only reach around $679,000

521
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:13,560
under the same conditions.

522
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:16,080
That's less than half the amount.

523
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:18,840
See, those extra 10 years of compounding

524
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,760
really boost the final amount

525
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:24,210
because there's more time for
interest to build on interest.

526
00:21:24,210 --> 00:21:26,190
So the younger you start, the better.

527
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:28,230
Not only will you have time on your side,

528
00:21:28,230 --> 00:21:31,530
but you'll also typically
earn less at a younger age,

529
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:34,170
placing you in a lower tax bracket.

530
00:21:34,170 --> 00:21:36,270
This means you'll keep
more of your earnings

531
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:38,190
because you won't be taxed as heavily

532
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:40,800
compared to when you
earn more later in life.

